Fountains Abbey, Yorkshire
This UNESCO-listed site is home to a beautiful ruined abbey and over 300 hectares of countryside. It also features a stunning display of snowdrops, supposedly dating back to the 1800s when an aristocrat planted snowdrops to spell out his name on the banks of the river. Abbey and garden open from 10am to 5pm, every day except Fridays. Park open every day, 7am to 9pm.
