Stars beat the dot.com kids in race for riches
By Simon English in New York
12:01AM BST 06 Sep 2001
THE film star Tom Cruise and the golfer Tiger Woods joined the ranks of the youngest and wealthiest in America this year as entertainers edged out businessmen in the race for riches. Fortune magazine's third annual survey of the 40 richest self-made Americans aged under 40 places the 39-year-old actor at number 19, with an estimated personal wealth of $251 million (£180 million). Cruise is one of six celebrities to join the elite group, which last year included only the basketball star Michael Jordan on the list of mostly internet entrepreneurs. The stock market slump and plunge in the value of many of the top technology companies has seen many of America's young business titans decline into comparative poverty. Even those entrepreneurs who did hold their own are considerably poorer. The average wealth of the 40 has dived by almost half to $935 million.
Related Articles
TV stars do the business
17 Aug 2001
Tiger Woods, 25, scrapes into this list at number 40 with a personal fortune of merely $160 million. Last year the poorest of the 40 was worth three times that figure. Last year's list included 13 billionaires, while this year there are only five. Michael Dell, the 36-year-old whizz-kid who leads Dell Computers, remains top with a net worth of $16 billion (£11 billion). Jeff Bezos, the founder of Amazon.com, remains fifth, yet his fortune has dropped from $4 billion to $1.2 billion. Jordan, at number 13 with $398 million, the rapper Sean Combs, at 22 with $231 million, and the actor Jim Carrey are among the entertainers who have shown sharper business acumen than some of those in commerce. Nicholas Stein at Fortune said they had exploited what had been a huge power shift in the industry in the past few years. "An elite cadre of celebrity athletes, actors and musicians transformed themselves from mere entertainers into powerful brands," he said. Fortune spent months analysing financial documents to come up with the list, which specifically excludes those who inherited their money. Knocking on the door of the prestigious survey is Britney Spears who, at 19, is already worth $46 million. Julia Roberts, with $138 million, is one blockbuster film away from staking her claim. USA
